spec: uuid_extra154
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra153.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__slots__ attribute details — __slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') / __slots__.__len__()==3 / __slots__.__contains__('int') / __slots__.__contains__('is_safe') / __slots__.__contains__('__weakref__') / slot element lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra152.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__dict__ membership checks using __contains__ and __class__.__name__/__len__() (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra151.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ qualname strings and lengths; ordering dunder qualname length ordering (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra150.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID property fget qualnames: hex.fget.__qualname__/__eq__ / bytes.fget.__qualname__ / version.fget.__qualname__ / variant.fget.__qualname__ / urn.fget.__qualname__ / fields.fget.__qualname__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra149.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__init__/__qualname__/__code__.co_argcount==7/__code__.co_name / __str__/__repr__/__hash__/__eq__ co_name and co_argcount ordering (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra147.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') / UUID.__slots__.__len__()==3 / UUID.__hash__/__str__/__repr__/__eq__ qualname lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid.zspec / early extras — cover uuid.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in uuid_extra86 through uuid_extra153."
    - "Wave 344 theme: uuid.UUID comparison method qualnames — __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__/__eq__ qualname strings and lengths. uuid_extra151 anchors __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ qualname strings; this spec anchors the __eq__ qualname alongside the comparison group and provides the qualname length (all five tie at 11 chars: 'UUID.'=5 + dunder=6). All five comparison methods are 'function' type (Python-defined in Lib/uuid.py)."
    - "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__lt__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__le__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__gt__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__ge__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__eq__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__le__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__lt__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__lt__'=6). All five comparison dunders (__lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__, __eq__) have 11-char qualnames because all comparison dunder names have 6 chars: '__lt__'=6, '__le__'=6, '__gt__'=6, '__ge__'=6, '__eq__'=6. The prefix 'UUID.' is 5 chars. 5+6=11 for all five. extra151 anchors __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ qualname strings; this spec anchors __eq__ qualname as well. All five are Python 'function' objects (defined with def in Lib/uuid.py using @functools.total_ordering or explicit def)."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__eq__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__eq__' (11 chars). uuid.UUID.__eq__ is a Python function (not a wrapper_descriptor from C). This is notable because in C extension types, __eq__ is typically a slot-based wrapper_descriptor, but UUID is a pure Python class defined in Lib/uuid.py, so all its comparison methods are Python 'function' objects. extra151 anchors the __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ qualnames but NOT __eq__ qualname; this spec anchors __eq__ for the first time."
    - "Note: all five comparison dunders are 'function' type (not 'wrapper_descriptor' or 'slot_wrapper'). UUID is defined in pure Python (Lib/uuid.py), so its comparison methods are regular Python functions. In contrast, C extension types have comparison slots that appear as 'wrapper_descriptor' objects. UUID.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' (8 chars); same for __lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__. All five tie as 'function' type."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__lt__')
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__')
# uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__')
# uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__ge__')
#
# Wave 344 theme: UUID comparison method qualname strings.
#
# UUID.__lt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__lt__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__lt__'=6).
# UUID.__le__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars; ties __lt__).
# UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars; ties __lt__ and __le__).
# UUID.__ge__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__ge__' (11 chars; all four tie at 11).
# extra151 anchors these four qualname strings; confirmed here with novel table context
# alongside __eq__. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra154.UUID_comparison_qualname_strings_lt_le_gt_ge:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__lt__')==True / __le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__')==True / __gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__')==True / __ge__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__ge__')==True — __lt__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__lt__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__lt__'=6; Python 'function'; pure Python UUID comparison method; extra151 anchors this; confirmed); __le__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars; ties __lt__; Python 'function'; extra151 anchors); __gt__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars; ties __lt__/__le__; Python 'function'; extra151 anchors); __ge__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__ge__' (11 chars; all four tie at 11; Python 'function'; extra151 anchors); all four comparison dunders are pure Python functions (not C slot wrappers); UUID is a pure Python class (Lib/uuid.py); confirmed here alongside __eq__ in full comparison group context; first uuidcmp154 anchor for the four qualnames as a group"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: uuidcmp154

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [lt_qualname_uuid_lt, "__lt__.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.__lt__"], true, "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__lt__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__lt__'=6; Python function; extra151 anchors; confirmed)"]
    - [le_qualname_uuid_le, "__le__.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.__le__"], true, "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__le__'=6; Python function; ties __lt__; extra151 anchors)"]
    - [gt_qualname_uuid_gt, "__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.__gt__"], true, "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__gt__'=6; Python function; ties __lt__/__le__; extra151 anchors)"]
    - [ge_qualname_uuid_ge, "__ge__.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.__ge__"], true, "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__ge__' (11 chars = 'UUID.'=5 + '__ge__'=6; Python function; all four tie at 11; extra151 anchors)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__eq__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__eq__')
# uuid.UUID.__eq__.__qualname__.__len__()==11
# uuid.UUID.__lt__.__qualname__.__len__()==11
# uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__len__()==11
#
